ack unless you have auth and TLS in front."],[226,"tsv"],[492,"turbo build across packages"],[473,"Turborepo layout, scripts, and where hyper-pm packages live."],[590,"Turn on GitHub sync and set GITHUB_REPO — see GitHub sync."],[8,"type: info"],[98,"type: info"],[413,"type: info"],[545,"type: info"],[566,"type: info"],[586,"type: info"],[728,"type: info"],[789,"type: info"],[208,"type: warn"],[524,"type: warn"],[626,"type: warn"],[652,"type: warn"],[673,"type: warn"],[753,"type: warn"],[830,"type: warn"],[171,"Typical first run:"],[598,"Typical workflows"],[73,"update"],[109,"update"],[124,"update"],[585,"Use --format text (a global option before the subcommand) for human-readable tables during exploration:"],[780,"Use it for readiness checks."],[746,"Use it when you prefer clicking and forms over shell flags, or when you want a stable POST /api/run endpoint for scripts (with the server fixing repo and temp paths)."],[672,"Use it when you want an AI assistant to read epics, list tickets, run doctor, or drive sync, without hand-copying JSON between chat and the terminal."],[677,"Use node with the absolute path to apps/hyper-pm-mcp/dist/main.mjs (see examples below)."],[559,"Use Node.js 20+ and pnpm. The required pnpm version is pinned under packageManager in the repo root package.json."],[592,"User guide"],[170,"Uses global options only — there are no init-specific flags beyond those shared flags (repo, data branch, remote, sync, GitHub slug, etc.)."],[181,"Valid --type values"],[45,"Validate event log replay"],[172,"Validates that the event log on the data branch reads and replays without structural errors. Exits non-zero when problems are found."],[512,"Variable"],[679,"Variable"],[761,"Variable"],[564,"Verify:"],[730,"Web UI (hyper-pm-web)"],[609,"Web UI (hyper-pm-web) — local browser app plus POST /api/run for scripts; the server pins --repo, --temp-dir, and --format json."],[539,"Web UI: POST /api/run"],[569,"Web: run hyper-pm-web from your repo (or set HYPER_P